                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/257.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Peru</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs informed that Chile has purchased munitions of war
                    in Germany immediate delivery and that 7,000 men still in Tarata, Arica, and
                    Tacna will be increased to 50,000 in furtherance of positive plan of attack of
                    which Peru knows. Chilean advantage land and naval forces, with natural alliance
                    from boundary disputes, presents conditions that will involve all at Chilean
                    instigation. Defenseless, Peru invokes mediating Powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
